name: TEXT
description: (.doc, .readme, .text, .txt) - a text file

name: FASTA
description: A text-based format which begins with a single-line description, followed by lines of sequence data

name: PDF
description: (.pdf) - portable document format

name: EXCEL
description: (.xls, .xlsx) - Microsoft office spreadsheet files

name: GFF
description: (.gff) - The General Feature Format (GFF) is used for describing genes and other features of DNA, RNA and protein sequences

name: UNKNOWN
description: any other file format not defined here

name: FASTQ
description: (.fq, .fastq) - the FASTQ format stores sequences (usually nucleotide sequence) and Phred qualities in a single file.

name: CONTIG
description: (.contig) - the CONTIG format is a direct output from the SOAPdenovo alignment program

name: VCF
description: (.vcf) - the Variant Call Format (VCF) is a text file format for representing eg SNPs, InDels, CNVs, SVs, microsatellites, genotypes

name: PNG
description: (.png) - portable network graphics

name: IPR
description:
(.ipr) - the Web Gene Ontology (WEGO) Annotation format consists of the protein ID, followed by column(s) that are the IPR (InterPro) ID(s):
CR_ENSP00000334840
CR_ENSMMUP00000018123 	IPR000504 	IPR003954
CR_ENSP00000333725 	IPR001781 	IPR015880 	IPR007087 	IPR001909

See WEGO: a web tool for plotting GO annotations

name: KEGG
description:
(.kegg) - the Web Gene Ontology (WEGO) Annotation format consists of the protein ID, followed by column(s) that are the KEGG (Kyoto Encyclopedia of Genes and Genomes) ID(s):
CR_ENSMMUP00000031408 	ko03010
CR_ENSP00000364815 	ko00970 	ko00290
CR_ENSP00000414605 	ko05146 	ko04510 	ko04512

See WEGO: a web tool for plotting GO annotations

name: WEGO
description:
(.wego) - the Web Gene Ontology (WEGO) Annotation format consists of the protein ID, followed by column(s) that are the GO ID(s):
Bmb015379_2_IPR001092
Bmb003749_1_IPR006329 	GO:0009168 	GO:0003876
Bmb006173_1_IPR000909 	GO:0007165 	GO:0004629 	GO:0007242

See WEGO: a web tool for plotting GO annotations

name: WIG
description: (.wig) - the output file from TopHat is a UCSC wigglegram of alignment coverage

name: RPKM
description:
(.rpkm) - Gene expression levels are calculated by Reads Per Kilobase per Million (RPKM) mapped reads eg 1kb transcript with 1000 alignments in a sample of 10 million reads (out of which 8 million reads can be mapped) will have RPKM = 1000/(1 * 8) = 125:
ENSP00000379387 	15.5651433366423 	6002951 	289 	3093
ENSP00000349977 	24.7483107230444 	6002951 	398 	2679
ENSP00000368887 	24.6477413647837 	6002951 	174 	1176

name: AGP
description:
(.agp) - the Accessioned Golden Path (AGP) file describes the assembly of a larger sequence object from smaller objects:
chr1 	1 	1972671 	0 	W 	scaffold43 	1 	1972671 	m
chr1 	1972672 	3061819 	1 	W 	scaffold8 	1 	1089148 	p
chr1 	3061820 	3181505 	2 	W 	scaffold548 	1 	119686 	m
chr1 	3181506 	4176151 	3 	W 	scaffold313 	1 	994646 	m

The large object can be a contig, a scaffold (supercontig), or a chromosome.
See AGP Specification v2.0

name: TAR
description: (.tar) - an archive containing other files

name: BAM
description: (.bam) - the Binary Alignment/Map (BAM) format is the compressed binary version of the Sequence Alignment/Map (SAM) format, a compact and index-able representation of nucleotide sequence alignments.

name: BIGWIG
description: (.bw) - the BIGWIG format is for storing dense, continuous data (such as GC percent, probability scores, and transcriptome data) that will be displayed in the UCSC Genome Browser as a graph. BIGWIG files are created initially from wiggle (WIG) type files, using the program wigToBigWig.

name: MAF
description: (.maf) - the Multiple Alignment Format (MAF) stores a series of multiple alignments at the DNA level between entire genomes.

name: CHAIN
description: (.chain) - the CHAIN format describes a pairwise alignment that allow gaps in both sequences simultaneously and is used by the UCSC Genome Browser.

name: NET
description: (.net) - the NET file format is used to describe the axtNet data that underlie the net alignment annotations in the UCSC Genome Browser

name: QUAL
description: (.qual) - the QUAL file format represents base quality score file for NextGen data (similar in format to fasta)

name: QMAP
description: (.qmap) - QMAP files are generated for methylation data from an internal BGI pipeline

name: RAW
description: (.raw) - Mass Spectrometry data format

name: SFF
description: sequence format file for Roche 454 nucleotide sequences.

name: wmv
description: Windows movie file format

name: WORD
description: a MS word document

name: LSM
description: Laser Scanning Microscope format

name: TIF
description: Tagged Image File Format

name: GZIP
description: GNU zip compressed file

name: MATLAB
description: MatLab Script

name: CSV
description: Comma Separated Variables table

name: AVI
description: Audio Video Interleaved (AVI) format is a file container that allows synchronous audio-with-video playback.

name: TSV
description: Tabular data represented as tab-separated values in a text file.

name: JPG
description: Joint Picture Group file format for lossy graphics file. Sequence of segments with markers. Begins with byte of 0xFF and follows by marker type.

name: BED
description: Browser Extensible Data (BED) format of sequence annotation track, typically to be displayed in a genome browser. BED detail format includes 2 additional columns (http://genome.ucsc.edu/FAQ/FAQformat#format1.7) and BED 15 includes 3 additional columns for experiment scores (http://genomewiki.ucsc.edu/index.php/Microarray_track).

name: TrackDB
description: declaration file for UCSC browsers track dataset display charateristics, see https://genome.ucsc.edu/goldenPath/help/trackDb/trackDbHub.html for details

name: XML
description: Data in XML format can be serialised into text, or binary format. eXtensible Markup Language (XML) format.

name: Newick
description: Phylogenetic tree Newick (text) format.

name: FASTA-aln
description: Fasta format for (aligned) sequences.

name: Cytoscape
description: Format of the cytoscape input file of gene expression ratios or values are specified over one or more experiments.

name: BLAST results
description: Format of results of a sequence database search using some variant of BLAST. This includes score data, alignment data and summary table.

name: BAI
description: BAM indexing format

name: CIGAR
description: Compact Idiosyncratic Gapped Alignment Report format is a compressed (run-length encoded) pairwise alignment format. It is useful for representing long (e.g. genomic) pairwise alignments. See http://wiki.bits.vib.be/index.php/CIGAR for more details.

name: DOC
description: microsoft word format

name: DOCX
description: microsoft word format

name: BMP
description: bitmap image file, is a raster graphics image file format used to store bitmap digital images independently of the display device

name: GIF
description: Graphics Interchange Format is a bitmap image format that uses lossless compression
